# Typing Standards

- All function signatures must have type hints for parameters and return types.
- All Pydantic models must use explicit field types. No `Any` without justification.
- Use `list[str]` not `List[str]` (modern Python syntax, no typing imports for builtins).
- Return types must be explicit, including `-> None` for functions that return nothing.
